ADDITIONAL NOTES SPECIFIC TO THIS PROJECT

1. Maintainer's Commercial Rights

   Notwithstanding the NonCommercial clause above, the project maintainer,
   Shu Zhang, holds additional commercial rights granted by contributors
   under the project's Contributor License Agreement (see CLA.md).
   These rights allow the maintainer to:

     - Publish commercial printed editions of The Brewing Bible
     - License the content for inclusion in commercial products,
       services, and platforms (including but not limited to iGulu
       hardware and software)
     - Offer paid subscription services derived from the content
     - Sublicense the content to commercial partners

   These maintainer-only commercial rights do not affect the public's
   rights under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0. The open-source content remains freely
   available to everyone in perpetuity.

2. Contributors Retain Ownership

   Contributors retain full copyright over their submitted content.
   Contributing to The Brewing Bible does not transfer ownership of any
   contribution. Contributors are free to use, publish, sell, or
   otherwise exploit their own work elsewhere.

3. Attribution Practice

   When the work or any substantial portion of it is used or adapted, the
   following attribution is recommended:

     "Based on The Brewing Bible, maintained by Shu Zhang and contributors,
      licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.
      https://github.com/iGulu666/igulu-home-brewing-bible"

4. Trademark Notice

   "The Brewing Bible" name and associated logos are not licensed under
   CC BY-NC-SA 4.0. Use of the name for derivative or fork projects is
   not permitted without separate written permission from the maintainer.

